==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shoelace
<hw>Shoe"lace</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>a length of cord for tying the
upper parts of a shoe together. Commercial <ex>shoelaces</ex> usually
come in different lengths, and have each end confined in a narrow
plastic tube for convenience in inserting the cords through the holes in
a shoe upper. Also called <altname>shoestring</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shoemaker</ent>⟦br⟧
